    {
      "instruction": "<p>Top, tail, and grate your <strong>carrot[s]</strong></p><p>Combine your <strong>gram flour</strong> and 1 tbsp<span class=\"text-purple\"> [1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span><strong> flour </strong>in a large bowl with your <strong>curry powder</strong>, <strong>half</strong> your <strong>nigella seeds</strong> (you'll use the rest later!) and 6 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[9 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[12 tbsp]</span> <strong>cold water</strong></p><p>Add a generous pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and<strong> pepper </strong>and give it a good mix up until there are no lumps – this is your <strong>pakora batter</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
